newsitem.title: USA: U.S. cash crudes end weaker on inventory pressures.
newsitem.headline: U.S. cash crudes end weaker on inventory pressures.

text.p: Market expectations for builds in weekly crude stock inventories and large funds rolling positions out of the February to March futures contract pushed outright U.S. cash crudes lower on Tuesday.
Traders said the cash grades softened as well, continuing to feel pressure from a well-supplied market.
Foreign crudes were sold into the U.S. Gulf Coast at steady to weaker price levels, squeezing the domestic sweet grades, traders said.
February West Texas Intermediate/Cushing ended around 10 cents lower at $25.05-15 a barrel, and Feb/Mar WTI at 53 cts.
